05fc5a5e11e4a7ebf35b21a0a94615f50112a874.flavortext:

a6b16edfc2c542dd134b42781c87ab4494bc661f.flavortext: GraFight is a returning champ, and one of the very few bots to have made it to every single RSL event in Minnesota. GraFight is an RSL favorite - nicknamed "The Roomba of Doom".

8da5b2c83f835527a6ef7deccaa932fcacc8a29c.name: Gary
8da5b2c83f835527a6ef7deccaa932fcacc8a29c.flavortext:
Controller has to be held sideways
Uses a lifter
Relies on duct tape

6c7fe02750cb898532e3ecc26525f30b95aa7af4.name: Blight
6c7fe02750cb898532e3ecc26525f30b95aa7af4.flavortext: Blight is a 4WD vert. It features large titanium plows which provide ample front-end defense.

cdbf58baffb9c814788279fc2b1820407083f642.name: Robot A
cdbf58baffb9c814788279fc2b1820407083f642.flavortext: A rectangular test platform with delusions of grandeur.

7a38491269c8e4e4d202a74283086acd15f0132f.flavortext: 2nd Try is a googly-eyed horizontal spinner with a massive weapon - watch out!

e93a43189f16c1dd5ee6faead5beb7d7bdb02dc3.flavortext: Cookie Cutter utilizes a vertical spinner and wedge. It is a returning RSL champion, having taken 1st at the first RSL Legion tournament.

2adbc860090f99b460d3c684f7485233d12a2838.name: Monolith
2adbc860090f99b460d3c684f7485233d12a2838.flavortext: An Umbreon-inspired shuffling horizontal spinner. Monolith's 130  gram blade will pack a punch!

707116407cd6fbb3d789bcfa0558ee0047015f80.name: banila and aboras
707116407cd6fbb3d789bcfa0558ee0047015f80.flavortext: The Demon capsule monsters return in antweight form

a762d490807d1de275a94823178d08a4ff68cd64.flavortext:
- Uses heat and vertical spinner
- Brand new
- Mix of nylon and PLA

7f3bfd6b1674937bbf51b55ff336d72b7b142742.name: Painkiller
7f3bfd6b1674937bbf51b55ff336d72b7b142742.flavortext: Faster than a bullet. Terrifying scream. Enraged and full of anger. He is the Painkiller. This is the Painkiller.

8b6f89003c7aabcb897a7d3e2680a4533e118df8.name: Pork Lift
8b6f89003c7aabcb897a7d3e2680a4533e118df8.flavortext: Pork Lift is a pig-themed lifter, capable of using either a forked or wedge configuration. Both include googly eyes. Oink!

a5c37bb73968c08ed9c7959d57d30a4155572cde.name: Necessary Evil
a5c37bb73968c08ed9c7959d57d30a4155572cde.flavortext: Necessary Evil is a Betz Botz Kit bot and utilizes either forks or a wedge.

2248e382fdcfb0ca66451c031b340af302ef97f7.name: Lawnmower of Chaos
2248e382fdcfb0ca66451c031b340af302ef97f7.flavortext: Lawnmower of Chaos (L.M.O.C.) is an overhead, full-body bar spinner. Also, it could possibly cut grass, but we haven't tested it.

7e23ac0461a32a3fe0f8ee08621b2ff56f30b15f.name: Belladonna
7e23ac0461a32a3fe0f8ee08621b2ff56f30b15f.flavortext: Belladonna is a 2WD vertical spinner - aptly named after a deadly plant.

757d6a6bfb5c29713c6a1644cc2243a6703b8058.name: sash
757d6a6bfb5c29713c6a1644cc2243a6703b8058.flavortext: Sash is a fully upgraded kit bot! Seen here using a 2-wheel drive system and horizontal spinner.

690af089c0dc1d3a1d8ce1bf6e2d300750dd7b8a.name: RedDragon
690af089c0dc1d3a1d8ce1bf6e2d300750dd7b8a.flavortext: RedDragon is a TPU pusher bot, sporting a really cool sticker.

00706b5e9ede7f2fb6145370efd20ef72969df11.name: Neon
00706b5e9ede7f2fb6145370efd20ef72969df11.flavortext: Neon is a TPU pusher bot, with a large front wedge.

01d19bf031de83ac3444fbbf8b29a2e2abfbbc51.name: Jimmy Jazz
01d19bf031de83ac3444fbbf8b29a2e2abfbbc51.flavortext: Jimmy Jazz is a beta edition of the new Scalar 1 lb combat robot kit. Current record: 5 wins, 2 losses.

c92848b8c99c7fe1e9a9697fa92a0cc4b309c8b5.name: Johhny Crash
c92848b8c99c7fe1e9a9697fa92a0cc4b309c8b5.flavortext: Johhny Crash is a circular bot with a metal shell. It has fought in previous tournaments under the alias "Supernova".

388944a2341a5c3dcc4d74f0eb2509c309f678e5.name: Mini Marg
388944a2341a5c3dcc4d74f0eb2509c309f678e5.flavortext: Modified scalar with the same back fins as Marg

1778011d76abab63f8683ec00f560f177275bc4b.name: Mars
1778011d76abab63f8683ec00f560f177275bc4b.flavortext: All of Night Sky Robotics bots have celestial themes to them. Mars features a vertical drum spinner with hardened steel blades, aluminum chassis covered Ultra High Molecular Weight Polyethylene. This bot is driven by 9 year old Rory, while his sister Molly helps in the pits and dad Matt builds and maintains the bot.

f16f98a788438f3dd9bbde103777cf1f1d00260e.name: Thebe
f16f98a788438f3dd9bbde103777cf1f1d00260e.flavortext: Thebe, daughter of Zeus, sharpens her hunting prowess with each passing day. As her skill intensifies, so too does the peril. Prepare for the rising challenge.

23812d15edee8ba212288dfcff9c7e913d1d7d2e.name: Metis
23812d15edee8ba212288dfcff9c7e913d1d7d2e.flavortext: Metis, the goddess of wisdom, teaches us the ways of combat and changes as the need arises.  What does she bring to the challenge this time and are you ready?

aa80ab26001974e2d0c210ca2895b3f0d367dee4.name: Soldier boy
aa80ab26001974e2d0c210ca2895b3f0d367dee4.flavortext: A modular spinner with a custom hub motor and treads.

59a5aa04b1c8e78ff5ef8339844bdafa5e755a12.name: Firaga
59a5aa04b1c8e78ff5ef8339844bdafa5e755a12.flavortext: Shell Spinner. Started building it 9pm the day before the event. What is sleep?

2848d196caf64d53d470e9c7b4bc6b7496a31ba6.name: Exogenesis
2848d196caf64d53d470e9c7b4bc6b7496a31ba6.flavortext: Exogenesis is using a flipper - very cool!

270d5b4a5212498c8e548b2f97b2c2e1297f4459.name: Hypersonic
270d5b4a5212498c8e548b2f97b2c2e1297f4459.flavortext: Here to check your top armor

1bcaed689e60dbb55e879d07255749968bea0c4c.flavortext: A dual drum bristle bot. MRCA Bristle Bonus - Weight=1.75lbs/793g

e52c854d5631eec7468ba4727b4c77eb745f2965.name: Demo
e52c854d5631eec7468ba4727b4c77eb745f2965.flavortext: You break it, You buy it.

84d020414d17790f9b7fa29fbccae3a7571c1a42.name: Stabitha
84d020414d17790f9b7fa29fbccae3a7571c1a42.flavortext: I don't get mad........ I get stabby

6b2c88193c8a88d3d7a5375fd96e4b9d9daba030.name: Rip and Tear
6b2c88193c8a88d3d7a5375fd96e4b9d9daba030.flavortext:
Rip & Tear, formerly Tornado of Destruction & Dad's Spinner, is a returning RSL finalist. It is a horizontal spinner that can cause some serious damage!
Just like Doom Guy, this bot rips and tears its way through the competition.

ae417d6490ea91148766ff0876f68c94c678c4ad.name: Tomahawk 2.0
ae417d6490ea91148766ff0876f68c94c678c4ad.flavortext: Aluminum Beater go brrrrrrr. Started as a college capstone project.

3e03cfafb7b34a6fcd84c0a7aabccc8ae8862f95.name: Stress Concentration
3e03cfafb7b34a6fcd84c0a7aabccc8ae8862f95.flavortext: No info on this bot. We'll all be surprised!

b2f1b4110758e9e4c7766c104b0114ba43fa9abb.name: Marg
b2f1b4110758e9e4c7766c104b0114ba43fa9abb.flavortext: Modified scalar with the same back fins as Marg

cc3c6269b165672c6b88efc3483c6265c12e29c2.name: Fairy Powerful
cc3c6269b165672c6b88efc3483c6265c12e29c2.flavortext: A 4-wheel drive drisk with a Sylveon-inspired paint scheme. This is the bot I've wanted to build ever since I decided to build robots.

08f1dcb1cbe5edacc763fed365ee46e5c05bb91e.name: Chaotic Destructor
08f1dcb1cbe5edacc763fed365ee46e5c05bb91e.flavortext: Big brother of Chaotic Rampage, Chaotic Destructor is coming into battle with some fierce hitting power. Sporting a 6 inch AR500 steel weapon, it's ready to deal massive damage!

0c22c226cfc58bcacbbf19991fe7ac0890f34054.name: The Trooper
0c22c226cfc58bcacbbf19991fe7ac0890f34054.flavortext: The Trooper is a returning RSL finalist. It's design is based on the D2 combat robot kit and it uses a titanium wedge.

670fcac9a1889fa8e1a8a5b5449ba46af76af257.name: Skippy
670fcac9a1889fa8e1a8a5b5449ba46af76af257.flavortext: Skippy is a returning RSL finalist. It utilizes a FingerTech beater bar.

de39b254e2f35f3d4f797fd9ac0debea7aee9b42.name: Specture
de39b254e2f35f3d4f797fd9ac0debea7aee9b42.flavortext: Both RSL and MRCA has seen the beetleweight version of Specture perform quite well - having taken second place at the Minnesota Monster Mash and first place at the MRCA Finals in 2023.

07e3c41341071a6466813370efbdc160b7e29d60.name: COYOTE TIME
07e3c41341071a6466813370efbdc160b7e29d60.flavortext: We don't have a picture of Coyote Time to confirm, but we're told that it's a D2 kit bot.

b7615ab0187c3e3edc489ef8795ed977ee455850.name: Weaponized Incompetence
b7615ab0187c3e3edc489ef8795ed977ee455850.flavortext:
This guy has a lifter does that count as weaponized?
Over 1/6th of this bots weight is in AR500 Steel
Over 1/6th of this bot knows what's it's doing so can it really be that incompetent?

2b80b68da6bfc335d725bb2c69dea4c0b5769e38.name: Kamikaze
2b80b68da6bfc335d725bb2c69dea4c0b5769e38.flavortext: Second weekend in a row of fighting.

9fb15f519a0ef53f2f7200d44d72350b3193e1f7.name: Robot C
9fb15f519a0ef53f2f7200d44d72350b3193e1f7.flavortext: Robot C is an undercutter that could be described as a cross between a scalar kit and a plastic poison kit. The arena floor knows what it did to deserve this.

b499f4df023943cbce0fae3e49e325ed66897f6a.name: Three Amigos
b499f4df023943cbce0fae3e49e325ed66897f6a.flavortext:
Inspired by Three Blind Mice, a team of three 1lb Repeat minibots that compete in Beetles.
This is the antweight version, with each one weighing in at 151 grams. With chonky TPU forks, fat urethane wheels and titanium cover plates over the electronics, we anticipate these to be quite robost.
A single one of them will happily bully a 1lb bot around the arena, so three of them will be a blast!

6a14cc241ee5f1e559bc8222bb191aa75fef46e1.name: TestBot
6a14cc241ee5f1e559bc8222bb191aa75fef46e1.flavortext: Don't look! This bot is a test of the system and ordinarily should not be visible!
